Title: E-human resource management (E-HRM) project: A systematic literature review
Source title: International Journal of Scientific and Technology Research
Authors with affiliations: Alexander, I., Bina Nusantara University, Indonesia; Wijaya, R., Bina Nusantara University, Indonesia
Abstract: Information Technology is the golden key in this era and it has changed how the way we live. One of the big impacts is in organizational process especially in Human Resource Management (HRM). With the help of Information Technology, it changed the way of t raditional HR into modern HR. One of the most popular technology for HRM is Electronic Human Resource Management (E-HRM). E-HRM is an application of information technology that allows managers, applicants and employees access to human resource related information and services through the Internet. In this study we focused to discuss the success factor of E-HRM project implementation and the challenge of implementing E-HRM project. The successful E-HRM implementation can be achieved if there are a support from top management and many factors. However, there are still many challenges for implementing E-HRM. With this kind of factor and challenge, organization must know what to do before implementing the E-HRM system. © 2020, International Journal of Scientific and Technology Research. All rights reserved.

Authors: Wijaya R., Christian V., Yuwananda Y.S., Alexander I.
Title: Temperature and humidity monitoring system in server room using raspberry Pi
Source title: International Journal of Scientific and Technology Research
Authors with affiliations: Wijaya, R., Bina Nusantara University, Indonesia; Christian, V., Bina Nusantara University, Indonesia; Yuwananda, Y.S., Bina Nusantara University, Indonesia; Alexander, I., Bina Nusantara University, Indonesia
Abstract: Server is a vital device and should be given more attention in active state. Important data like database or documents of web application are stored in server. The server must active for a long time and doing a heavy process, if the room temperature is not conducive it can cause a decrease of server performance. Because of this problem we proposed a monitoring system that can be used a solution for this problem. In this research we create a monitoring system using Raspberry Pi and DHT11 sensor. The results obtained that the temperature data received by the sensor are successfully sent and stored into a database using Raspberry Pi, the accuracy results of the DHT11 sensor used is 98.15% and the system successfully sent an e-mail notification when the temperature data received from the sensor passed the normal limit (20°C-25°C). © IJSTR 2019.
Author Keywords: Humidity sensor; Internet; Monitoring; MySQL database; Raspyberry Pi; Server; Temperature sensor

Title: Predicting indoor position using bluetooth low energy and machine learning
Source title: International Journal of Scientific and Technology Research
Authors with affiliations: Alexander, I., Bina Nusantara University, Indonesia; Kusuma, G.P., Bina Nusantara University, Indonesia
Abstract: Many people spend most of their time indoors.Providing localization services indoor will have many potential applications, such as navigation, requesting help and asset tracking.There are manyexistingpositioning techniques for indoor positioning system such as multilateration, trilateration and least square estimation.But theweakness of this existing positioning technique is that the results of predictionerrors are still very large. With the development of machine learning technique, many researchers had used machine learning techniquesfor indoor positioning system.However, the existing research still uses location classification, even though machine learning can be used as regression to predict location. In this study, we propose a positioning algorithm forindoor positioning system using Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE), fingerprinting approach and four machine learning regression: Artificial Neural Network Regression (ANN), Multiple Linear Regression (MLR), Random Forest Regression (RF) and Support Vector Regression (SVR). We compare theperformance in term of Mean of Error, Min of Error, Max of Error, Median of Error and 90 th Percentile of Error between four machine learning regression and the weighted sum method as a benchmark. The results obtained that allmachine learning regression has lowerMean of errorcompared to the weighted sum method. The SVR model has the best performance amongthemachine learning regression,whichyields134.92 cmofMean of error, 18.39cm ofMin of Error, 336.29 cmofMax of Error, 125.54cm ofMedian of Error and 216.65 cm of 90 th Percentile of Error. © 2019 IJSTR.
Author Keywords: Bluetooth low energy; Fingerprinting; Indoor position system; Localization; Machine learning; Sensor networks; Wireless technology

Title: Business Solution for Choosing Products Using Data Warehouse in Payment Solution
Source title: 1st 2018 Indonesian Association for Pattern Recognition International Conference, INAPR 2018 - Proceedings
Affiliations: Computer Science Department, BINUS Graduate Program-Master of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta 11480, Indonesia
Authors with affiliations: Alexander, I., Computer Science Department, BINUS Graduate Program-Master of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta 11480, Indonesia; Rassetiadi, R., Computer Science Department, BINUS Graduate Program-Master of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta 11480, Indonesia; Garcia, S., Computer Science Department, BINUS Graduate Program-Master of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta 11480, Indonesia; Girsang, A.S., Computer Science Department, BINUS Graduate Program-Master of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta 11480, Indonesia; Isa, S.M., Computer Science Department, BINUS Graduate Program-Master of Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta 11480, Indonesia
Abstract: In this increasingly modern world, marketing is a very interesting job. If more products are purchased by customers then the salary received is also higher. One of important issue in PT. XYZ is how to choose which products are now being sought/searched by the customer. The goal of this paper is to create a system and report that can help marketing to choose which product suitable to be offered to customer. This paper proposes a data warehouse development through methodology designed by Kimball and Ross. Furthermore, the data can be analyzed using OLAP and then displayed on the dashboard. With this business solution, PT. XYZ can process and choose what kind of products are suitable for customer relatively faster. The result shows that the system can choose which products are suitable to be offered to customer from the dashboard display. © 2018 IEEE.

Authors: Atmadja W., Liawatimena S., Lukas J., Nata E.P.L., Alexander I.
Title: Hydroponic system design with real time OS based on ARM Cortex-M microcontroller
Source title: IOP Conference Series: Earth and Environmental Science
Affiliations: Computer Engineering Department, Faculty of Engineering, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, Indonesia
Authors with affiliations: Atmadja, W., Computer Engineering Department, Faculty of Engineering, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, Indonesia; Liawatimena, S., Computer Engineering Department, Faculty of Engineering, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, Indonesia; Lukas, J., Computer Engineering Department, Faculty of Engineering, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, Indonesia; Nata, E.P.L., Computer Engineering Department, Faculty of Engineering, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, Indonesia; Alexander, I., Computer Engineering Department, Faculty of Engineering, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, Indonesia
Abstract: Hydroponic is the process of growing plants without soil, plant root flooded or moist with nutrient-rich solutions in inert material. Hydroponics has become a reality for greenhouse growers in virtually all climates. Large hydroponic installations exist throughout the world for growing flowers, vegetables and some short period fruit like tomato and cucumber. In soilless culture, we must maintain stable pH and conductivity level of nutrient solution to make plant grow well, large variation of pH of certain time will poisoned plant. This paper describes development complete automation hydroponic system, from maintaining stable nutrient composition (conductivity and pH), grow light, and monitor plant environment such as CO2, temperature and humidity. The heart of our automation is ARM Cortex-M4 from ST Microelectronic running ARM mbed OS, the official Real Time Operating System (RTOS) for ARM Cortex-M microcontroller. Using RTOS gives us flexibility to have multithreaded process. Results show that system capable to control desired concentration level with variation of less than 3%, pH sensor show good accuracy 5.83% from pH value 3.23-10. Growing light intensity measurement show result 105 μmol/m2/s therefore we need turn on the light at least 17 hours/day to fulfil plant light requirement. RTOS give good performance with latency and jitter less than 15 us, system overall show good performance and accuracy for automating hydroponic plant in vegetative phase of growth. © 2017 Published under licence by IOP Publishing Ltd.
